State MSM Profile: New Mexico

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in New Mexico

An estimated 17,968 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in New Mexico in 2013, representing 0.4% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 762,051 adult men of New Mexico, 2.4% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in New Mexico resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (74.8%). No MSM in New Mexico resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and New Mexico, 2013

MSM in New Mexico Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in New Mexico, Bernalillo County had the largest population of MSM at 7,299, representing 40.6% of all MSM in the state. Torrance County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in New Mexico at 4.2%. This was greater than the percentage for New Mexico as a whole, which was 2.4% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in New Mexico Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Albuquerque Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Albuquerque MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in New Mexico at 9,307, or 51.8% of all MSM in the state. Of the 329,012 adult men in Albuquerque, an estimated 2.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Santa Fe Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Santa Fe MSA had a population of 1,809 MSM, or 10.1% of all MSM in New Mexico. Of the 55,855 adult men in Santa Fe, an estimated 3.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Las Cruces Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Las Cruces MSA had a population of 1,682 MSM, or 9.4% of all MSM in New Mexico. Of the 75,438 adult men in Las Cruces, an estimated 2.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Farmington Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Farmington MSA had a population of 635 MSM, or 3.5% of all MSM in New Mexico. Of the 45,267 adult men in Farmington, an estimated 1.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
